==================================================================================================================================Lesson 13 = Daily Life: Page 41-51
I) A) Change the verbs into the potential forms :
  1) hanasu = hanaseru
  2) suru = dekiru 
  3) iku = ikeru
  4) naru = nerareru
  5) kuru = korareru
  6) miru = mirareru 
  7) yameru = yamamameru
  8) kariru = karirareru
  9) nomu = nomeru
  10) matsu = materu
  11) oyogu = oyokeru 
  12) hataraku = hatarakeru
  13) amu = ameru
2) B) Describe the things mary can do : 
  1) Japanese song = meari- san wa nihongo no uta ga utae masu 
  2) Violin = meari- san wa viorin ga hike masu
  3) karate = meari- san wa karate ga deki masu
  4) sushi = meari- san wa sushi ga taberare masu
  5) pizza = meari- san wa piza ga tsukure masu
  6) motorbike = meari- san wa biku ni nore masu
  7) car = meari- san wa kuruma ga unten de ki masu
  8) sweater = meari- san wa se-ta- ga ame masu
  9) kanji = meari- san wa kanji ga takusan kake masu
  10) wake up = meari- san wa yaku okirare masu
  11) hot bath = meari- san wa atsui ofuro ni haieru
